{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id621a2885-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s151"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"151"},"text":"§ 151.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Deposits in bank by disbursing agents","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Any United States Indian agent, superintendent, or other disbursing agent of the Indian Service may deposit Indian moneys, individual or tribal, coming into his hands as custodian, in such national bank or banks as he may select: ","children":[{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided","children":[],"tail":", That the bank or banks so selected by him shall first execute to said disbursing agent a bond, with approved surety, in such an amount as will properly safeguard the funds to be deposited. Such bond shall be subject to the approval of the Secretary of the Interior."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id621a2886-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1908-04-30/ch153"},"text":"Apr. 30, 1908, ch. 153","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/35/73"},"text":"35 Stat. 73","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1910-06-25/ch431/s1"},"text":"June 25, 1910, ch. 431, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/36/855"},"text":"36 Stat. 855","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1928-03-03/ch122"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1928, ch. 122","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/45/161"},"text":"45 Stat. 161","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1934-04-30/ch169"},"text":"Apr. 30, 1934, ch. 169","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/48/648"},"text":"48 Stat. 648","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id621a2887-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id621a2888-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id621a2889-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This section is also set out in the last two provisos of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t25/s372"},"text":"section 372 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id621a288a-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id621a288b-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Indian Agents","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The services of Indian agents have been dispensed with. See note set out under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t25/s64"},"text":"section 64 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"id621a288c-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id621a288d-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For transfer of functions of other officers, employees, and agencies of Department of the Interior, with certain exceptions, to Secretary of the Interior, with power to delegate, see Reorg. Plan No. 3 of 1950, §§ 1, 2, eff. ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1950-05-24"},"text":"May 24, 1950","children":[],"tail":", 15 F.R. 3174, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/1262"},"text":"64 Stat. 1262","children":[],"tail":", set out in the Appendix to Title 5, Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of disbursement functions of all Government agencies with certain exceptions to the Fiscal Service, Treasury Department, see note set out under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t25/s53"},"text":"section 53 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
